{"title_page": "Sambalpur University", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Sambalpur University\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image_name = Sambalpur_university_logo.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| motto = Vidyaya Vindatemrutam ([[Sanskrit]]), Meaning : ''That is education which liberate''\n| established = {{start date|1967}}\n| type = [[Public university|Public]]\n| affiliation = [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]], [[National Assessment and Accreditation Council|NAAC]]\n| endowment = \n| chancellor = [[Governor of Odisha]]\n| superintendent = \n| vice_chancellor = Deepak Kumar Behera<ref>{{cite web|title=Sambalpur University :: Administration Hierarchy|url=https://www.suniv.ac.in/page.php?page=administration-hierarchy|website=www.suniv.ac.in|accessdate=25 December 2017}}</ref><ref>https://orissadiary.com/amp/prof-dr-deepak-kumar-behera-appointed-new-vice-chancellor-sambalpur-university/</ref>\n| undergrad = \n| postgrad = \n| doctoral = \n| city = [[Sambalpur]]\n| state = [[Odisha]]\n| country = [[India]]\n| coor = {{coord|20.473|85.891}}\n| campus = \n| free_label = \n| free = \n| colours = \n| website = {{url|http://www.suniv.ac.in/}}\n| logo = \n| footnotes = \n| staff = \n| faculty = \n}}\n\n'''Sambalpur University''' is located in [[Burla, India|Burla]] town, of district [[Sambalpur]], [[India]], in the [[States and territories of India|Indian state]] of [[Odisha]].<ref name=\"SambalpurHome1\">{{Cite web\n |url        = http://suniv.ac.in/\n |title      = Sambalpur University\n |accessdate = 2011-06-05\n |publisher  = Sambalpur University\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sambalpur.nic.in/public-utility/sambalpur-university/|title=sambalpur.nic.in}}</ref> Popularly known as Jyoti Vihar, it offers courses at the undergraduate and post-graduate levels. Governor of Odisha is the [[Chancellor (education)|Chancellor]] of the university. The campus is located 15&nbsp;km away from Sambalpur.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Su-maingate.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Samabalpur University old gate back to '90s]]\nOn 10 December 1966 the Sambalpur University Act was passed by the [[Odisha Legislative Assembly|Odisha Legislature]] for establishment of a University in the Western part of Odisha. This institute started from 1 January 1967. The first Vice-Chancellor was Prof. [[Parasuram Mishra]]. The University started functioning in 1967 in a rented private building at Dhanupali, Sambalpur; then in a government building at Ainthapali, Sambalpur. In 1973 the University was shifted to the present campus named Jyoti Vihar at Burla.\n\n==Location==\nThe present campus of the University is located at Burla, 2&nbsp;km away from NH 6. The campus of this university is in the vicinity of Mahanadi Coal Fields Limited, [[Veer Surendra Sai University of Technology, Burla|VSSUT]]<ref name=\"VSSUThome1\">{{Cite web\n |url        = http://www.vssut.ac.in/\n |title      = Veer Surendra Sai University of Technology, Odisha\n |accessdate = 2011-06-05\n |publisher  = Veer Surendra Sai University of Technology\n}}</ref> and located close to [[Hirakud Dam]].\n\n==Infrastructure and facilities==\n[[File:Mahodadhi Hostel Sambalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Mahodadhi Hostel]]\n[[File:Brahmaputra 1st Gents Hostel, Sambalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Brahmaputra 1st Gents Hostel]]\n[[File:Biju Patnaik Auditorium Sambalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Biju Patnaik Auditorium]]\n[[File:Bhagirathi 3rd Boys hostel, Sambalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Bhagirathi 3rd boys Hostel]]\n[[File:IB Hostel or Boys Hostel for SC-ST-OBC.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Ib Hostel]]\n[[File:I.I.M-S Auditorium Samabalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|I.I.M Auditorium]]\nSambalpur University is located at Burla town, Western Odisha. The university is spreaded over 670 acre surrounded by dense reserve forest of Burla town. This university is said to be knowledge hub of Western Odisha.\n\nThere are postgraduate hostels in the university campus out of which seven are for girls(''Narmada Ladies hostel'', ''Pravavati Devi Ladies Hostel'',  ''Silver Jubilee ladies hostel'', ''M.C.L Coalfield Ladies hostel (new)'', ''Baitarani Ladies Hostel'', ''Indravati Ladies Hostel, I.I.M-S Ladies Hostel)'' and eight are for boys ''(Bramhaputra Boys Hostel, Mahanadi Boys Hostel, Bhagirathi Boys Hostel, Academic Staff Hostel, Mahodadhi M.phil Hostel, Golden Jubilee Boys Hostel, I.I.M-S Boys Hostel, I.B hostel or SC/ST/OBC Boys Hostel)''. The university provides basic facilities to the boarders in the hostels like common room with television, reading room with newspaper and magazine, guest room, first aid, STD telephone booth, canteen etc. There are two nationalized banks ''(State Bank Of India and U.C.O Bank)'', one post-office, one Health Center, 2 Auditorium Biju Patnaik Auditorium and I.I.M Auditorium, one Police-Out Post, one faculty house and one community center have been established in the university campus for providing services to students/teachers and employees in the campus.\n\nAdmission to PG diploma, M.A, M. Sc, M.Tech, M.Phil, M.C.A, M.B.A and P.hD courses are being conducted through an entrance examination.\n\n==Affiliated colleges==\n{{Main|List of colleges affiliated to the Sambalpur University}}\nThere are about 196 colleges affiliated to Sambalpur University excluding four other colleges SLB Medical College, Nababharat Shiksha Parishad, Sardar Raza's Medical College and Sarala Nursing College with totalling more than 200 colleges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.suniv.ac.in/upload/List_of_Colleges%20_Aff.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=2019-12-23|access-date=2019-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223081635/https://www.suniv.ac.in/upload/List_of_Colleges%20_Aff.pdf|archive-date=23 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.suniv.ac.in/docs/List-of-Affiliated-Colleges-01.05.2013-sent.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=2019-12-23|access-date=2019-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223082004/https://www.suniv.ac.in/docs/List-of-Affiliated-Colleges-01.05.2013-sent.pdf|archive-date=23 December 2019}}</ref>\nColleges that are afflicted to Sambalpur University belong to the districts of Western Odisha namely [[Sundergarh district|Sundargarh]], [[Debagarh district|Deogarh]], [[Jharsuguda district|Jharsuguda]], [[Sambalpur district|Sambalpur]], [[Bargarh district|Bargarh]], [[Balangir district|Balangir]], [[Subarnapur district|Sonpur]](earlier called Subarnapur), [[Boudh district|Boudh]], [[Nuapada district|Nuapada]], [[Kalahandi district|Kalahandi]] and one [[Angul district|Angul's]] sub division [[Athmallik|Athmalik]].\n\n== Academics==\n===Undergraduate Course===\n+3 Arts/ Science/ Commerce, LLB, BBA-LLB B.A.-LLB, B.Ed, BCA, Bachelor of Journalism & Mass Communication, Bachelor of Library & Information Science, Bachelor of Physical Education (BPEd), BAMS, BHMS, MBBS, B. Sc. (Nursing) and Bachelor in Physiotherapy are offered by this University.\n\n===Post Graduate Department===\nThe postgraduate (PG) departments of Sambalpur University offers PG Diploma, MA, M Sc., M Tech, M.Phil, PhD, and D.Sc degrees. All the departments are actively involved in research and well equipped for research facility for NET/JRF/GATE students.<ref name=\"SambalpurResearch1\">{{Cite web|url=http://suniv.ac.in/rechresearchfacility.html|title=Research Facility|publisher=Sambalpur University|accessdate=2011-06-05}}</ref> This University offers a limited numbers of scholarships for students to pursue their research work in various fields.  Following are the courses taught in various fields.<ref name=\"SambalpurUniversityPG1\">{{Cite web|url=http://suniv.ac.in/admpostgraduate.html|title=Post Graduate|publisher=Sambalpur University|accessdate=2011-06-05}}</ref>\n\nThe university provides post-graduation education in 42 subjects through 30 post-graduation departments, with Education and Centre of foreign Languages as the recently added department continuing from the year 2018.\n\n'''P.G departments available in University Campus:'''\n\n#'''''P.G Department of Anthropology''''' - Established in 1976.\n#'''''Department of Biotechnology and Bioinformatics (Self financing)''''' - It was established in 2016. It provides self financing course in  M.Sc. Biotechnology 2016, Bioinformatics (ii) M.Sc. Bioinformatics 2016, P.G. Diploma in Bioinformatics 2018.\n#'''''Nano Research Centre''''' - Established in 2017.\n#'''''Department of Business Administration''''' - It provides regular as well as self financing courses in Executive MBA estd. in 2004, MBA Rural Management estd. in 2012, MBA (Agri-Business) estd. in 2017. Recently there was a need felt to remove the self financing courses of M.B.A Rural Management due to less applicant, from the year 2020-21 the course may be discontinued according to the department coordinator.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/dec/16/sambalpur-university-may-scrap-mba-in-rural-management-course-2076783.html|title=Sambalpur University may scrap MBA in Rural Management course|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n#'''''School of Chemistry''''' - Established in 1969, provides regular courses including self finance such as in M.Sc. Applied Chemistry.\n#'''''Department of Computer Sciences and Applications''''' - Established in 1988.\n#'''''Department of Earth Science''''' - Established in 1984. Provides regular, including self financing in M.Tech. Geospatial Technology 2011\n#'''''M Tech in Geo spactial Technology''''' -  Established in 2012.\n#'''''P.G Department of Economics''''' - Established in 1971. Provides regular, including self financing in (M.B.A, financial Management).\n#'''''Centre for foreign Language (Self Financing)''''' - Established in 2018, it offers Chinese Language, and French Language only.\n#'''''Department of Education (Self Financing)'''''- Established in 2017, recently established in the year 2018 with self financing in Integrated B.Ed-M.Ed.\n#'''''Department of English''''' - Established in 1969.\n#'''''P.G Department of Environmental Science''''' - Established in 1989, provides regular including self financing in M.Tech. Environmental Science & Engineering, M.Tech. in Safety, Health & Environmental Technology.\n#'''''Department of Hindi''''' - Established in 2010.\n#'''''P.G Department of History''''' - Established in 1969, there is one Museum in History department which is in the name of professor N.K Sahoo, called Prof. N. K Sahoo Museum.<ref name=\"NMFMhome12\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.namami.org/convervation.htm|title=Manuscript Conservation Centres|publisher=[[National Mission for Manuscripts]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120506234603/http://www.namami.org/convervation.htm|archivedate=2012-05-06|accessdate=2011-06-05}}</ref> There is a Manuscript Conservation Centre (MCC) under the [[National Mission for Manuscripts]] which was established in 2003.\n#'''''P.G Department of Home Science''''' - Established in 1976.\n#'''''P. G Department of Law''''' - Established in 1986.\n#'''''Library and Information Science''''' - Established in 1976.\n#'''''School of Life Sciences''''' - Established in 1971, provides regular as well as self financing in M.Sc. Microbiology.\n#'''''School of Mathematical Sciences''''' - Established in 1969.\n#'''''Department of Odia''''' - Established in 1968.\n#'''''School of Performing Arts (Dance & Drama)''''' - Established in 2010, imparts education in Dance and Drama.\n#'''''Political Science and public Administration''''' - Established in 1967, M.A. in Political Science, P.G. Diploma in Human Rights Education, Certificate Course in Human Rights Education.\n#'''''School of Physics''''' - Established in 1969,Provides regular, including self financing in M.Sc. Medical Physics.\n#'''''Sanskrit''''' - Established in 2017, provides self financing course in M.A Sanskrit.\n#'''''P.G Department of Sociology''''' - Established in 1991.\n#'''''Department of Statistics''''' - Established in 1976.\n#'''''P.G Department of Social Work- Master of Social work (Self Financing)''''' - Established in 2017, provides self financing course in Master of Social Work.\n#'''''Master in Performing Arts''''' - Established in 2010.\n#'''''P.G Department of Food Science Technology (FST & FS) and Nutrition (Self Financing)''''' - Established in 2010, recently established in 2017 with self financing course in M.Tech. Food Sc. & Tech., M.Sc. Food Science, M.Sc. Food Sc. & Nutrition\n\n'''Miscellaneous buildings include:'''\nAdministrative block, P.G Council, Private Examination Cell, Sbi Bank Branch with 2 atm, Post Office, Health centre, Sambalpur University, Market Complex, Prof.Bhubaneshwar Behera Central Library, Sambalpur University New Library, UCO bank, Kantapali 1 atm, Home Cum Canteen ( University Canteen), Central Canteen 1, Canteen 2, U.G.C - H.R.D.C Lecture Hall, U.S.I.C Sambalpur University, U.G.C Human Resources Development Center, Sambalpur University, Bhagirathi Canteen (Hostel Canteen), I.B Canteen (Hostel Canteen)\n\n'''Post Graduate courses include'''\nPost Graduate courses that are offered by this institution include Anthropology, Business Administration, Chemistry, Earth Science, Economics, English, Environmental Science, Hindi, History, Home Science, Library and Information Science, Life Science, Mathematics, Odiya, Performing Arts(Drama, Dance), Political Science and public administration, Sociology and Statistics.\n\n'''2 Post Graduate Diploma Courses include:'''\nComputer Application and Human Rights Education\n\n'''1 Certificate course include:'''\nHuman Rights Education\n\n'''2 Professional courses include:'''\nIt include L.L.M. and M.B.A.\n\n'''9 Self financing courses include:'''\n\nM. Sc. in Applied Chemistry, M. Tech. in Environmental Science & Engineering, M. Tech. in Geospatial Technology, M. Sc. in Biotechnology, Executive M.B.A., MBA (Financial Management), Master of Social Work (MSW), M. Sc. in Food Science & Nutrition, M. Tech. in Food Science & Technology\n\n'''19 M. Phil Courses include:'''\nAnthropology, Business Administration, Chemistry, Computer Science, Earth Science, Economics, English, Environmental Science, History, Home Science, Library&Information Science, Life Sciences, Mathematics, Odia, Political Science, Public Administration, Physics, Sociology, Statistics.\n\n'''28 P.hd Course include:'''\nAnthropology, Chemistry, Earth Science, Economics, English, Environmental Science, History, Home Science, Library & Information Science, Law, Life Sciences, Mathematics, Odia, Political Science & Public Administration, Physics, Sociology, Statistics, Food Science and Technology, Environmental Engineering, Bio Technology, Computer Science, Information Technology, Bio informatics, Electronic and Engineering, Linguistics, Remote Sensing and GIS, Management, MSW\n\n'''On campus distance education'''\n\nThe Directorate of Distance and Continuing Education has started in the year 1998.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sambalpuruniversityddce.com/aboutus.html|title=Distance Education{{!}}Sambalpur University{{!}}Orissa|date=2015-03-16|access-date=2019-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316100408/http://www.sambalpuruniversityddce.com/aboutus.html|archive-date=16 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nIt include P.G. Diploma in Industrial Chemistry, P.G. Diploma in Environment Education & Management, P.G. Diploma in Industrial Safety & \nManagement, P.G. Diploma in Mass Communication & Journalism, \nP.G. Diploma in Library Automation & Networking, P.G. Diploma in \nSocial Work & HRD, P.G. Diploma in Remote Sensing & GIS, MBA \n(3 years).\n\nThis university includes two autonomous constituent institute they are [[Sambalpur University Institute of Information Technology|S.U.I.I.T (Sambalpur University Institute of Information Technology)]] and [[Indian Institute of Management Sambalpur|I.I.M-S (Indian Institute of Management, Sambalpur)]].\n\n'''Course offered by S.U.I.I.T''' are B. Tech. in ECE, B. Tech. in CSE, B. Tech. in EEE, M. Sc, in \nElectronics, M. Sc. in Computer Science, M. Sc. in Bioinformatics, \nMCA, M. Tech in CS, M. Tech in ESD, M. Tech in CSE.\n\n===Other courses include===\nUniversity also offers DEM, Diploma in Regional Arts & Commerce, PGDCA, PGDIRPM.\n\n==Gangadhar National Award==\n{{Main|Gangadhar National Award}}\nThis award is given in the field of Literature. The award was first given in 1991 but the procedure of giving award was started in 1989. There is a delay of 1 year due to a long process of choosing an awadee, if the awadee won the prize for the year 2019 then he will get his award in the Year 2021, and the award of 2017 will be given in the year 2019. It is awarded on the celebration day of Sambalpur University foundation day, Foundation day is celebrated every year in January. \nTill now 28 poets have been awarded on various Indian Languages.\nCash prize of Rs 50,000, angavastra, citation, a memento and a copy of Gangadhar Meher: Selected Works (An anthology of Gangadhar Meher's Poetry in English translation) is given to receipt of Gangadhar National Award.\n\n==Notables==\n===Notable alumni===\nNotable alumni in politics include Naba Kishore das, [[Bhakta Charan Das]], [[Pradipta Kumar Naik]], [[Prabhas Kumar Singh]].\n\nNotable alumni in Indian film Indian film industry include producer [[Jitendra Mishra]], [[Ashutosh Pattnaik]].\n\nNotable alumni in science include mathematician [[Indulata Sukla]], [[Gadadhar Misra]]. [[Bhubaneswar Behera]], botanist, Indian ecologist and environmentalist [[Madhab Chandra Dash]] and educationist [[Parshuram Mishra]] who is the recipient of Padma Shri and neurosurgeon [[B. K. Misra]], recipient of [[Dr. B. C. Roy Award]], the highest medical honour in India.<ref>{{cite web |title=Basant Kumar Misra, President NSI 2008 |url=http://www.neurosocietyindia.org/site/Past-president/Basant%20Kumar%20Misra,%20President%20NSI%202008.pdf |website=neurosocietyindia.org |accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nNotable alumni in poetry include [[Gopal Rath]], [[Hussain Rabi Gandhi]] , [[Mayadhar Swain]], [[Srinivas Udgata]], [[Mayadhar Swain]].\n\n===Other notables===\n[[Prem Ram Dubey]] who became dean of law of Sambalpur University in 1967, [[Ananta Charan Sukla]] scholar of comparative literature, literary criticism, and philosophy. [[Priyambada Mohanty Hejmadi]] who was a former vice chancellor of Sambalpur University.\n\n[[Dilip Tirkey|Dilip tirky]] a sportsperson who received honorary doctorate from Sambalpur University.\n\n[[Sriballav Panigrahi]] who was the member of the Senate and Syndicate, Sambalpur University from 1969 to 1972.\n\n== Notable events ==\n\n==== Ceremony ====\nOdisha Governor [[Ganeshi Lal]], Principal Secretary to the PMO, [[Pramod Kumar Misra|Pramod Kumar Mishra]] attended 30th convocation ceremony 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orissadiary.com/amp/odisha-governor-principal-secretary-to-the-pmo-pk-mishra-attended-30th-convocation-ceremony-of-sambalpur-university/|title=Odisha Governor, Principal Secretary to the PMO, PK Mishra attended 30th convocation ceremony of #Sambalpur University|date=2019-11-29|website=OdishaDiary|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n==== Disputes ====\nThere had been attempts to make self financing courses like B.Ed and M.Ed eligible for central and state level teacher eligibility test.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/nov/06/bed-med-students-launch-padayatra-over-recognition-2057813.html|title=B.Ed, M.Ed students launch padayatra over 'recognition'|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> There are at least 150 students who are studying integrated courses offered from 2017. This integrated course is also offered by other universities and autonomous colleges like [[North Orissa University|North Odisha University]], [[Fakir Mohan University]] and [[Rajendra College Balangir]] since 2016.\n\nThe first year batch of 2017 in Sambalpur University integrated B.Ed and M.Ed students were exempted from applying [[Odisha Teacher Eligibility Test|Odisha Teacher Eligibility test]], [[Central Teacher Eligibility Test|Central Teacher Eligibility test]] and the Odisha Secondary School Teacher Eligibility test for not displaying their degree in their website, for which they were not able to apply for various extrance examination .<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2019 there was a strike conducted by the students of Medical physics for not recognising one of the self financing course of physics department called M.Sc Medical physics. The course offered by this university was not recognised by [[Atomic Energy Regulatory Board]] (AERB) for which students cannot apply for posts like a Medical physicist. Students have called for hunger strike for its exclusion form being recognised by [[AERB]] .<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/dec/09/no-aerb-recognition-for-sambalpur-varsitys-medical-physics-course-2073539.html|title=Recognition for Sambalpur University Medical physics course|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhubaneswar/protest-in-varsity-over-aerb-recognition-row/articleshow/72463581.cms|title=Protest in Sambalpur University over AERB recognition row {{!}} Bhubaneswar News - Times of India|last=Dec 11|first=Subrat Mohanty {{!}} TNN {{!}}|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-12-12|last3=Ist|first3=16:18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhubaneswar/without-aerb-nod-fate-of-37-su-students-hangs-in-balance/articleshow/72430209.cms|title=Without AERB nod, fate of 37 Sambalpur University students hangs in balance {{!}} Bhubaneswar News - Times of India|last=Dec 9|first=Subrat Mohanty {{!}} TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-12-12|last3=Ist|first3=14:08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/dec/04/msc-medical-physics-students-demand-aerb-recognition-2071221.html|title=MSc Medical Physics students demand AERB recognition|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref>\n\nThere had been delay in the results of 1st year students in Bhima Bhoi Medical College and Hospital(BBMCH) which started functioning in September 2018, affiliated to the Sambalpur University for which students were on strike.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://odishatv.in/odisha/mbbs-students-demonstrate-for-delay-in-publication-of-results-in-odisha-419523|title=MBBS Students Demonstrate Over Delay In Publication Of Results In Odisha {{!}} OTV|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\n==== Changes in system ====\nOdisha government in 2019 approved that 155 colleges which are under Sambalpur University their academic activities will be transferred to new universities which will commence from June 1, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/odisha-govt-starts-process-to-appoint-vcs-in-two-new-universities/articleshow/72032293.cms|title=Odisha govt starts process to appoint VCs in two new universities - Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> Government Autonomous College, Bhawanipatna and Rajendra Autonomous College, Balangir  will be upgraded to University which will later take colleges under their jurisdiction.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhubaneswar/odisha-staff-shortage-ails-75-year-old-college/articleshow/72157902.cms|title=Odisha: Staff shortage ails 75-year-old college {{!}} Bhubaneswar News - Times of India|last=Nov 21|first=TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-11-29|last3=Ist|first3=13:18}}</ref>\n\nThere had been attempts to make this a Central University.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.orissapost.com/gangadeb-seeks-central-univ-tag-to-sambalpur-varsity/|title=Gangadeb seeks Central Univ tag to Sambalpur varsity - OrissaPOST|date=2019-12-12|website=Odisha News, Odisha Latest news, Odisha Daily - OrissaPOST|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Sambalpur University Institute of Information Technology]]\n*[[List of colleges affiliated to the Sambalpur University]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.suniv.ac.in/  University Website]\n\n{{Universities in Odisha}}\n{{Department of Higher Education, Odisha}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Sambalpur]]\n[[Category:Universities in Odisha]]\n[[Category:Department of Higher Education, Odisha]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1967]]\n[[Category:1967 establishments in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Sambalpur University\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image_name = Sambalpur_university_logo.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| motto = Vidyaya Vindatemrutam ([[Sanskrit]]), Meaning : ''That is education which liberate''\n| established = {{start date|1967}}\n| type = [[Public university|Public]]\n| affiliation = [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]], [[National Assessment and Accreditation Council|NAAC]]\n| endowment = \n| chancellor = [[Governor of Odisha]]\n| superintendent = \n| vice_chancellor = Deepak Kumar Behera<ref>{{cite web|title=Sambalpur University :: Administration Hierarchy|url=https://www.suniv.ac.in/page.php?page=administration-hierarchy|website=www.suniv.ac.in|accessdate=25 December 2017}}</ref><ref>https://orissadiary.com/amp/prof-dr-deepak-kumar-behera-appointed-new-vice-chancellor-sambalpur-university/</ref>\n| undergrad = \n| postgrad = \n| doctoral = \n| city = [[Sambalpur]]\n| state = [[Odisha]]\n| country = [[India]]\n| coor = {{coord|20.473|85.891}}\n| campus = \n| free_label = \n| free = \n| colours = \n| website = {{url|http://www.suniv.ac.in/}}\n| logo = \n| footnotes = \n| staff = \n| faculty = \n}}\n\n'''Sambalpur University''' is located in [[Burla, India|Burla]] town, of district [[Sambalpur]], [[India]], in the [[States and territories of India|Indian state]] of [[Odisha]].<ref name=\"SambalpurHome1\">{{Cite web\n |url        = http://suniv.ac.in/\n |title      = Sambalpur University\n |accessdate = 2011-06-05\n |publisher  = Sambalpur University\n}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sambalpur.nic.in/public-utility/sambalpur-university/|title=sambalpur.nic.in}}</ref> Popularly known as Jyoti Vihar, it offers courses at the undergraduate and post-graduate levels. Governor of Odisha is the [[Chancellor (education)|Chancellor]] of the university. The campus is located 15&nbsp;km away from Sambalpur.\n\n==History==\n[[File:Su-maingate.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Samabalpur University old gate back to '90s]]\nOn 10 December 1966 the Sambalpur University Act was passed by the [[Odisha Legislative Assembly|Odisha Legislature]] for establishment of a University in the Western part of Odisha. This institute started from 1 January 1967. The first Vice-Chancellor was Prof. [[Parasuram Mishra]]. The University started functioning in 1967 in a rented private building at Dhanupali, Sambalpur; then in a government building at Ainthapali, Sambalpur. In 1973 the University was shifted to the present campus named Jyoti Vihar at Burla.\n\n==Location==\nThe present campus of the University is located at Burla, 2&nbsp;km away from NH 6. The campus of this university is in the vicinity of Mahanadi Coal Fields Limited, [[Veer Surendra Sai University of Technology, Burla|VSSUT]]<ref name=\"VSSUThome1\">{{Cite web\n |url        = http://www.vssut.ac.in/\n |title      = Veer Surendra Sai University of Technology, Odisha\n |accessdate = 2011-06-05\n |publisher  = Veer Surendra Sai University of Technology\n}}</ref> and located close to [[Hirakud Dam]].\n\n==Infrastructure and facilities==\n[[File:Mahodadhi Hostel Sambalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Mahodadhi Hostel]]\n[[File:Brahmaputra 1st Gents Hostel, Sambalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Brahmaputra 1st Gents Hostel]]\n[[File:Biju Patnaik Auditorium Sambalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Biju Patnaik Auditorium]]\n[[File:Bhagirathi 3rd Boys hostel, Sambalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Bhagirathi 3rd boys Hostel]]\n[[File:IB Hostel or Boys Hostel for SC-ST-OBC.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Ib Hostel]]\n[[File:I.I.M-S Auditorium Samabalpur University.jpg|thumb|right|250px|I.I.M Auditorium]]\nSambalpur University is located at Burla town, Western Odisha. The university is spreaded over 670 acre surrounded by dense reserve forest of Burla town. This university is said to be knowledge hub of Western Odisha.\n\nThere are postgraduate hostels in the university campus out of which seven are for girls(''Narmada Ladies hostel'', ''Pravavati Devi Ladies Hostel'',  ''Silver Jubilee ladies hostel'', ''M.C.L Coalfield Ladies hostel (new)'', ''Baitarani Ladies Hostel'', ''Indravati Ladies Hostel, I.I.M-S Ladies Hostel)'' and eight are for boys ''(Bramhaputra Boys Hostel, Mahanadi Boys Hostel, Bhagirathi Boys Hostel, Academic Staff Hostel, Mahodadhi M.phil Hostel, Golden Jubilee Boys Hostel, I.I.M-S Boys Hostel, I.B hostel or SC/ST/OBC Boys Hostel)''. The university provides basic facilities to the boarders in the hostels like common room with television, reading room with newspaper and magazine, guest room, first aid, STD telephone booth, canteen etc. There are two nationalized banks ''(State Bank Of India and U.C.O Bank)'', one post-office, one Health Center, 2 Auditorium Biju Patnaik Auditorium and I.I.M Auditorium, one Police-Out Post, one faculty house and one community center have been established in the university campus for providing services to students/teachers and employees in the campus.\n\nAdmission to PG diploma, M.A, M. Sc, M.Tech, M.Phil, M.C.A, M.B.A and P.hD courses are being conducted through an entrance examination.\n\n==Affiliated colleges==\n{{Main|List of colleges affiliated to the Sambalpur University}}\nThere are about 196 colleges affiliated to Sambalpur University excluding four other colleges SLB Medical College, Nababharat Shiksha Parishad, Sardar Raza\u2019s Medical College and Sarala Nursing College with totalling more than 200 colleges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.suniv.ac.in/upload/List_of_Colleges%20_Aff.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=2019-12-23|access-date=2019-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223081635/https://www.suniv.ac.in/upload/List_of_Colleges%20_Aff.pdf|archive-date=23 December 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.suniv.ac.in/docs/List-of-Affiliated-Colleges-01.05.2013-sent.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=2019-12-23|access-date=2019-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223082004/https://www.suniv.ac.in/docs/List-of-Affiliated-Colleges-01.05.2013-sent.pdf|archive-date=23 December 2019}}</ref>\nColleges that are afflicted to Sambalpur University belong to the districts of Western Odisha namely [[Sundergarh district|Sundargarh]], [[Debagarh district|Deogarh]], [[Jharsuguda district|Jharsuguda]], [[Sambalpur district|Sambalpur]], [[Bargarh district|Bargarh]], [[Balangir district|Balangir]], [[Subarnapur district|Sonpur]](earlier called Subarnapur), [[Boudh district|Boudh]], [[Nuapada district|Nuapada]], [[Kalahandi district|Kalahandi]] and one [[Angul district|Angul's]] sub division [[Athmallik|Athmalik]].\n\n== Academics==\n===Undergraduate Course===\n+3 Arts/ Science/ Commerce, LLB, BBA-LLB B.A.-LLB, B.Ed, BCA, Bachelor of Journalism & Mass Communication, Bachelor of Library & Information Science, Bachelor of Physical Education (BPEd), BAMS, BHMS, MBBS, B. Sc. (Nursing) and Bachelor in Physiotherapy are offered by this University.\n\n===Post Graduate Department===\nThe postgraduate (PG) departments of Sambalpur University offers PG Diploma, MA, M Sc., M Tech, M.Phil, PhD, and D.Sc degrees. All the departments are actively involved in research and well equipped for research facility for NET/JRF/GATE students.<ref name=\"SambalpurResearch1\">{{Cite web|url=http://suniv.ac.in/rechresearchfacility.html|title=Research Facility|publisher=Sambalpur University|accessdate=2011-06-05}}</ref> This University offers a limited numbers of scholarships for students to pursue their research work in various fields.  Following are the courses taught in various fields.<ref name=\"SambalpurUniversityPG1\">{{Cite web|url=http://suniv.ac.in/admpostgraduate.html|title=Post Graduate|publisher=Sambalpur University|accessdate=2011-06-05}}</ref>\n\nThe university provides post-graduation education in 42 subjects through 30 post-graduation departments, with Education and Centre of foreign Languages as the recently added department continuing from the year 2018.\n\n'''P.G departments available in University Campus:'''\n\n#'''''P.G Department of Anthropology''''' - Established in 1976.\n#'''''Department of Biotechnology and Bioinformatics (Self financing)''''' - It was established in 2016. It provides self financing course in  M.Sc. Biotechnology 2016, Bioinformatics (ii) M.Sc. Bioinformatics 2016, P.G. Diploma in Bioinformatics 2018.\n#'''''Nano Research Centre''''' - Established in 2017.\n#'''''Department of Business Administration''''' - It provides regular as well as self financing courses in Executive MBA estd. in 2004, MBA Rural Management estd. in 2012, MBA (Agri-Business) estd. in 2017. Recently there was a need felt to remove the self financing courses of M.B.A Rural Management due to less applicant, from the year 2020-21 the course may be discontinued according to the department coordinator.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/dec/16/sambalpur-university-may-scrap-mba-in-rural-management-course-2076783.html|title=Sambalpur University may scrap MBA in Rural Management course|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n#'''''School of Chemistry''''' - Established in 1969, provides regular courses including self finance such as in M.Sc. Applied Chemistry.\n#'''''Department of Computer Sciences and Applications''''' - Established in 1988.\n#'''''Department of Earth Science''''' - Established in 1984. Provides regular, including self financing in M.Tech. Geospatial Technology 2011\n#'''''M Tech in Geo spactial Technology''''' -  Established in 2012.\n#'''''P.G Department of Economics''''' - Established in 1971. Provides regular, including self financing in (M.B.A, financial Management).\n#'''''Centre for foreign Language (Self Financing)''''' - Established in 2018, it offers Chinese Language, and French Language only.\n#'''''Department of Education (Self Financing)'''''- Established in 2017, recently established in the year 2018 with self financing in Integrated B.Ed-M.Ed.\n#'''''Department of English''''' - Established in 1969.\n#'''''P.G Department of Environmental Science''''' - Established in 1989, provides regular including self financing in M.Tech. Environmental Science & Engineering, M.Tech. in Safety, Health & Environmental Technology.\n#'''''Department of Hindi''''' - Established in 2010.\n#'''''P.G Department of History''''' - Established in 1969, there is one Museum in History department which is in the name of professor N.K Sahoo, called Prof. N. K Sahoo Museum.<ref name=\"NMFMhome12\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.namami.org/convervation.htm|title=Manuscript Conservation Centres|publisher=[[National Mission for Manuscripts]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120506234603/http://www.namami.org/convervation.htm|archivedate=2012-05-06|accessdate=2011-06-05}}</ref> There is a Manuscript Conservation Centre (MCC) under the [[National Mission for Manuscripts]] which was established in 2003.\n#'''''P.G Department of Home Science''''' - Established in 1976.\n#'''''P. G Department of Law''''' - Established in 1986.\n#'''''Library and Information Science''''' - Established in 1976.\n#'''''School of Life Sciences''''' - Established in 1971, provides regular as well as self financing in M.Sc. Microbiology.\n#'''''School of Mathematical Sciences''''' - Established in 1969.\n#'''''Department of Odia''''' - Established in 1968.\n#'''''School of Performing Arts (Dance & Drama)''''' - Established in 2010, imparts education in Dance and Drama.\n#'''''Political Science and public Administration''''' - Established in 1967, M.A. in Political Science, P.G. Diploma in Human Rights Education, Certificate Course in Human Rights Education.\n#'''''School of Physics''''' - Established in 1969,Provides regular, including self financing in M.Sc. Medical Physics.\n#'''''Sanskrit''''' - Established in 2017, provides self financing course in M.A Sanskrit.\n#'''''P.G Department of Sociology''''' - Established in 1991.\n#'''''Department of Statistics''''' - Established in 1976.\n#'''''P.G Department of Social Work- Master of Social work (Self Financing)''''' - Established in 2017, provides self financing course in Master of Social Work.\n#'''''Master in Performing Arts''''' - Established in 2010.\n#'''''P.G Department of Food Science Technology (FST & FS) and Nutrition (Self Financing)''''' - Established in 2010, recently established in 2017 with self financing course in M.Tech. Food Sc. & Tech., M.Sc. Food Science, M.Sc. Food Sc. & Nutrition\n\n'''Miscellaneous buildings include:'''\nAdministrative block, P.G Council, Private Examination Cell, Sbi Bank Branch with 2 atm, Post Office, Health centre, Sambalpur University, Market Complex, Prof.Bhubaneshwar Behera Central Library, Sambalpur University New Library, UCO bank, Kantapali 1 atm, Home Cum Canteen ( University Canteen), Central Canteen 1, Canteen 2, U.G.C - H.R.D.C Lecture Hall, U.S.I.C Sambalpur University, U.G.C Human Resources Development Center, Sambalpur University, Bhagirathi Canteen (Hostel Canteen), I.B Canteen (Hostel Canteen)\n\n\n'''Post Graduate courses include'''\nPost Graduate courses that are offered by this institution include Anthropology, Business Administration, Chemistry, Earth Science, Economics, English, Environmental Science, Hindi, History, Home Science, Library and Information Science, Life Science, Mathematics, Odiya, Performing Arts(Drama, Dance), Political Science and public administration, Sociology and Statistics. \n\n'''2 Post Graduate Diploma Courses include:'''\nComputer Application and Human Rights Education\n\n'''1 Certificate course include:'''\nHuman Rights Education\n\n'''2 Professional courses include:'''\nIt include L.L.M. and M.B.A.\n\n'''9 Self financing courses include:'''\n\nM. Sc. in Applied Chemistry, M. Tech. in Environmental Science & Engineering, M. Tech. in Geospatial Technology, M. Sc. in Biotechnology, Executive M.B.A., MBA (Financial Management), Master of Social Work (MSW), M. Sc. in Food Science & Nutrition, M. Tech. in Food Science & Technology\n\n'''19 M. Phil Courses include:'''\nAnthropology, Business Administration, Chemistry, Computer Science, Earth Science, Economics, English, Environmental Science, History, Home Science, Library&Information Science, Life Sciences, Mathematics, Odia, Political Science, Public Administration, Physics, Sociology, Statistics.\n\n'''28 P.hd Course include:'''\nAnthropology, Chemistry, Earth Science, Economics, English, Environmental Science, History, Home Science, Library & Information Science, Law, Life Sciences, Mathematics, Odia, Political Science & Public Administration, Physics, Sociology, Statistics, Food Science and Technology, Environmental Engineering, Bio Technology, Computer Science, Information Technology, Bio informatics, Electronic and Engineering, Linguistics, Remote Sensing and GIS, Management, MSW\n\n'''On campus distance education''' \n\nThe Directorate of Distance and Continuing Education has started in the year 1998.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sambalpuruniversityddce.com/aboutus.html|title=Distance Education{{!}}Sambalpur University{{!}}Orissa|date=2015-03-16|access-date=2019-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316100408/http://www.sambalpuruniversityddce.com/aboutus.html|archive-date=16 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nIt include P.G. Diploma in Industrial Chemistry, P.G. Diploma in Environment Education & Management, P.G. Diploma in Industrial Safety & \nManagement, P.G. Diploma in Mass Communication & Journalism, \nP.G. Diploma in Library Automation & Networking, P.G. Diploma in \nSocial Work & HRD, P.G. Diploma in Remote Sensing & GIS, MBA \n(3 years).\n\nThis university includes two autonomous constituent institute they are [[Sambalpur University Institute of Information Technology|S.U.I.I.T (Sambalpur University Institute of Information Technology)]] and [[Indian Institute of Management Sambalpur|I.I.M-S (Indian Institute of Management, Sambalpur)]].\n\n'''Course offered by S.U.I.I.T''' are B. Tech. in ECE, B. Tech. in CSE, B. Tech. in EEE, M. Sc, in \nElectronics, M. Sc. in Computer Science, M. Sc. in Bioinformatics, \nMCA, M. Tech in CS, M. Tech in ESD, M. Tech in CSE.\n\n===Other courses include===\nUniversity also offers DEM, Diploma in Regional Arts & Commerce, PGDCA, PGDIRPM.\n\n==Gangadhar National Award==\n{{Main|Gangadhar National Award}}\nThis award is given in the field of Literature. The award was first given in 1991 but the procedure of giving award was started in 1989. There is a delay of 1 year due to a long process of choosing a awadee, if the awadee won the prize for the year 2019 then he will get his award in the Year 2021, and the award of 2017 will be given in the year 2019. It is awarded on the celebration day of Sambalpur University foundation day, Foundation day is celebrated every year in January. \nTill now 28 poets have been awarded on various Indian Languages.\nCash prize of Rs 50,000, angavastra, citation, a memento and a copy of Gangadhar Meher: Selected Works (An anthology of Gangadhar Meher's Poetry in English translation) is given to receipt of Gangadhar National Award.\n\n==Notables==\n===Notable alumni===\nNotable alumni in politics include Naba Kishore das, [[Bhakta Charan Das]], [[Pradipta Kumar Naik]], [[Prabhas Kumar Singh]].\n\nNotable alumni in Indian film Indian film industry include producer [[Jitendra Mishra]], [[Ashutosh Pattnaik]].\n\nNotable alumni in science include mathematician [[Indulata Sukla]], [[Gadadhar Misra]]. [[Bhubaneswar Behera]], botanist, Indian ecologist and environmentalist [[Madhab Chandra Dash]] and educationist [[Parshuram Mishra]] who is the recipient of Padma Shri and neurosurgeon [[B. K. Misra]], recipient of [[Dr. B. C. Roy Award]], the highest medical honour in India.<ref>{{cite web |title=Basant Kumar Misra, President NSI 2008 |url=http://www.neurosocietyindia.org/site/Past-president/Basant%20Kumar%20Misra,%20President%20NSI%202008.pdf |website=neurosocietyindia.org |accessdate=23 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nNotable alumni in poetry include [[Gopal Rath]], [[Hussain Rabi Gandhi]] , [[Mayadhar Swain]], [[Srinivas Udgata]], [[Mayadhar Swain]].\n\n===Other notables===\n[[Prem Ram Dubey]] who became dean of law of Sambalpur University in 1967, [[Ananta Charan Sukla]] scholar of comparative literature, literary criticism, and philosophy. [[Priyambada Mohanty Hejmadi]] who was a former vice chancellor of Sambalpur University.\n\n[[Dilip Tirkey|Dilip tirky]] a sportsperson who received honorary doctorate from Sambalpur University.\n\n[[Sriballav Panigrahi]] who was the member of the Senate and Syndicate, Sambalpur University from 1969 to 1972.\n\n== Notable events ==\n\n==== Ceremony ====\nOdisha Governor [[Ganeshi Lal]], Principal Secretary to the PMO, [[Pramod Kumar Misra|Pramod Kumar Mishra]] attended 30th convocation ceremony 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://orissadiary.com/amp/odisha-governor-principal-secretary-to-the-pmo-pk-mishra-attended-30th-convocation-ceremony-of-sambalpur-university/|title=Odisha Governor, Principal Secretary to the PMO, PK Mishra attended 30th convocation ceremony of #Sambalpur University|date=2019-11-29|website=OdishaDiary|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>\n\n==== Disputes ====\nThere had been attempts to make self financing courses like B.Ed and M.Ed eligible for central and state level teacher eligibility test.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/nov/06/bed-med-students-launch-padayatra-over-recognition-2057813.html|title=B.Ed, M.Ed students launch padayatra over 'recognition'|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref>There are atleast 150 students who are studying integrated courses offered from 2017. This integrated course is also offered by other universities and autonomous colleges like [[North Orissa University|North Odisha University]], [[Fakir Mohan University]] and [[Rajendra College Balangir]] since 2016.\n\nThe first year batch of 2017 in Sambalpur University integrated B.Ed and M.Ed students were exempted from applying [[Odisha Teacher Eligibility Test|Odisha Teacher Eligibility test]], [[Central Teacher Eligibility Test|Central Teacher Eligibility test]] and the Odisha Secondary School Teacher Eligibility test for not displaying their degree in their website, for which they were not able to apply for various extrance examination .<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn 2019 there was a strike conducted by the students of Medical physics for not recognising one of the self financing course of physics department called M.Sc Medical physics. The course offered by this university was not recognised by [[Atomic Energy Regulatory Board]] (AERB) for which students cannot apply for posts like a Medical physicist. Students have called for hunger strike for its exclusion form being recognised by [[AERB]] .<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/dec/09/no-aerb-recognition-for-sambalpur-varsitys-medical-physics-course-2073539.html|title=Recognition for Sambalpur University Medical physics course|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhubaneswar/protest-in-varsity-over-aerb-recognition-row/articleshow/72463581.cms|title=Protest in Sambalpur University over AERB recognition row {{!}} Bhubaneswar News - Times of India|last=Dec 11|first=Subrat Mohanty {{!}} TNN {{!}}|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-12-12|last3=Ist|first3=16:18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhubaneswar/without-aerb-nod-fate-of-37-su-students-hangs-in-balance/articleshow/72430209.cms|title=Without AERB nod, fate of 37 Sambalpur University students hangs in balance {{!}} Bhubaneswar News - Times of India|last=Dec 9|first=Subrat Mohanty {{!}} TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-12-12|last3=Ist|first3=14:08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/odisha/2019/dec/04/msc-medical-physics-students-demand-aerb-recognition-2071221.html|title=MSc Medical Physics students demand AERB recognition|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref>\n\nThere had been delay in the results of 1st year students in Bhima Bhoi Medical College and Hospital(BBMCH) which started functioning in September 2018, affiliated to the Sambalpur University for which students were on strike.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://odishatv.in/odisha/mbbs-students-demonstrate-for-delay-in-publication-of-results-in-odisha-419523|title=MBBS Students Demonstrate Over Delay In Publication Of Results In Odisha {{!}} OTV|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\n==== Changes in system ====\nOdisha government in 2019 approved that 155 colleges which are under Sambalpur University their academic activities will be transferred to new universities which will commence from June 1, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/home/education/news/odisha-govt-starts-process-to-appoint-vcs-in-two-new-universities/articleshow/72032293.cms|title=Odisha govt starts process to appoint VCs in two new universities - Times of India|website=The Times of India|access-date=2019-11-29}}</ref> Government Autonomous College, Bhawanipatna and Rajendra Autonomous College, Balangir  will be upgraded to University which will later take colleges under their jurisdiction.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bhubaneswar/odisha-staff-shortage-ails-75-year-old-college/articleshow/72157902.cms|title=Odisha: Staff shortage ails 75-year-old college {{!}} Bhubaneswar News - Times of India|last=Nov 21|first=TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2019|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-11-29|last3=Ist|first3=13:18}}</ref>\n\nThere had been attempts to make this a Central University.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.orissapost.com/gangadeb-seeks-central-univ-tag-to-sambalpur-varsity/|title=Gangadeb seeks Central Univ tag to Sambalpur varsity - OrissaPOST|date=2019-12-12|website=Odisha News, Odisha Latest news, Odisha Daily - OrissaPOST|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Also See==\n*[[Sambalpur University Institute of Information Technology]]\n*[[List of colleges affiliated to the Sambalpur University]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons Category}}\n*[http://www.suniv.ac.in/  University Website]\n\n{{Universities in Odisha}}\n{{Department of Higher Education, Odisha}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Sambalpur]]\n[[Category:Universities in Odisha]]\n[[Category:Department of Higher Education, Odisha]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1967]]\n[[Category:1967 establishments in India]]\n", "name_user": "Lakun.patra", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: atleast \u2192 at least, \u2019s \u2192 's, a awadee, \u2192 an awadee,", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.or